ps, hence \"classical\" geometrical\nsymmetries of Poisson type (via specialization) associated to the \"generalized\nsymmetry\" encoded by the original Hopf algebra over k. Both the main result and\nthe above mentioned application are illustrated via several examples of many\ndifferent kinds, which are studied in full detail.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Mar 2003 11:00:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 17 Mar 2003 13:16:25 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 14 Apr 2003 12:38:04 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 18 Apr 2003 22:51:52 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Tue, 24 Jun 2003 08:25:16 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Tue, 9 Sep 2003 13:13:16 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Wed, 24 Mar 2004 09:28:29 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Tue, 12 Dec 2006 16:23:50 GMT"},{"version":"v9","created":"Thu, 4 Oct 2012 21:40:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-10-08"}
